    longDescription:
      "Agoda's cashback claim rate model was trained only on fully expired bookings — those more than 180 days old — leaving the training signal perpetually stale. Before building a replacement, the project first validated that the staleness was genuinely harmful by decomposing the weighted claim rate into a behavior-shift component and an amount-distribution-shift component, confirming they move independently and that real behavior shifts were occurring. The new model reframes claim rate prediction as a survival analysis problem — asking 'will this booking claim today, given it hasn't claimed yet?' rather than 'will it ever claim?' — enabling training on 60-day-old bookings and daily prediction updates. This also fixes a systematic cost overestimation: the old model held predictions constant for unclaimed bookings, inflating expected cashback liability by over 20% during the claimable period.",
