    category: "Pricing Optimization",
    title: "Rewriting the Rules: A New Capping System for Pricing Optimization",
    shortDescription:
      "Replacing a sequential hard-capping algorithm with a simultaneous soft-capping system — transforming large \"insensitive\" regions of the optimization space into regions where price signals can actually be read and acted on.",
    longDescription:
      "Agoda's pricing RL model applied downlift and cashback caps sequentially — a design that inadvertently created large 'insensitive' regions where noise injections produced no measurable change in treatment, effectively blinding the model to pricing signals across a substantial share of production bookings. Three failures drove a full redesign: the sequential logic made the constraint space asymmetric, locked out cross-optimization between the two levers, and made it structurally difficult for marketing teams to substitute cashback for downlift in specific markets. The replacement represents the constraint space geometrically and rescales both levers simultaneously, ensuring every perturbation in the intended treatment produces a proportional, observable change in actual treatment. Convergence simulations confirmed the new system always reaches the true optimum; the old system could get permanently stuck.",
